In this press briefing, Press Secretary Robert Gibbs addresses various topics, including the bombings in Uganda, the oil spill, the Russian spying incident, the extension of middle-class tax cuts, the offshore drilling moratorium, the state of the economy, the situation in Haiti, the START treaty, and immigration reform. Gibbs also discusses the President's phone call with President Abbas, the Mama Grizzly ad, and the recess appointment of Dr. Berwick. He ends the briefing by mentioning the administration's upcoming HIV and AIDS policy announcement.